{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5689b402-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s332"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"332"},"text":"§ 332.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Marine industry training program","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Commandant shall, by policy, establish a program under which an officer, member, or employee of the Coast Guard may be assigned to a private entity to further the institutional interests of the Coast Guard with regard to marine safety, including for the purpose of providing training to an officer, member, or employee. Policies to carry out the program—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id5689b403-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s332/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" with regard to an employee of the Coast Guard, shall include provisions, consistent with sections 3702 through 3704 of title 5, as to matters concerning—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id5689b404-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s332/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the duration and termination of assignments;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id5689b405-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s332/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" reimbursements; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id5689b406-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s332/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" status, entitlements, benefits, and obligations of program participants; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id5689b407-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s332/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shall require the Commandant, before approving the assignment of an officer, member, or employee of the Coast Guard to a private entity, to determine that the assignment is an effective use of the Coast Guard’s funds, taking into account the best interests of the Coast Guard and the costs and benefits of alternative methods of achieving the same results and objectives.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5689b408-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/281/tV/s521/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–281, title V, § 521(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2956"},"text":"124 Stat. 2956","children":[],"tail":", § 59; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/281/tII/s221/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–281, title II, § 221(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3037"},"text":"128 Stat. 3037","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 314, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/tI/s104/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 104(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4196"},"text":"132 Stat. 4196","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 332, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXII/s7201/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXII, § 7201(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1675"},"text":"139 Stat. 1675","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5689b409-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5689b40a-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id5689b40b-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 332 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s2128"},"text":"section 2128 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5689b40c-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2025—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s314"},"text":"section 314 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s59"},"text":"section 59 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/281"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–281","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (a) designation and heading before “The Commandant” and struck out subsec. (b). Text of subsec. (b) read as follows: “Not later than the date of the submission each year of the President’s budget request under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1105"},"text":"section 1105 of title 31","children":[],"tail":", the Commandant shall submit to the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation of the Senate a report that describes—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) the number of officers, members, and employees of the Coast Guard assigned to private entities under this section; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) the specific benefit that accrues to the Coast Guard for each assignment.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
